# Providers

Every ticketing platform integration implements the same `TicketingProvider` interface. The attribution and rewards engines consume the interface, never provider-specific code.

## The interface

```ts
// src/lib/providers/types.ts

export type ProviderId =
  | 'weeztix'
  | 'manual_utm'
  | 'eventbrite'    // post-MVP
  | 'eventix'       // post-MVP — same company as Weeztix; check if same API
  | 'shopify'       // post-MVP
  | 'stripe';       // post-MVP

export type AuthenticityMechanism =
  | { kind: 'hmac'; algorithm: 'sha256'; header: string; encoding: 'hex' | 'base64' }
  | { kind: 'nonce'; header: string }
  | { kind: 'none' };

export interface ProviderCapabilities {
  nativeTrackers: boolean;
  webhooks: boolean;
  refundEvents: boolean;            // true if a dedicated trigger; false if inferred from updates
  refundInferenceField?: string;    // if refundEvents=false, the payload field signalling refund
  orderLookup: boolean;
  promoCodes: boolean;
  reconciliation: boolean;
  authenticity: AuthenticityMechanism;
  providerSuppliedIdempotencyHeader?: string;  // e.g. 'OpenTicket-Dedupe-Key'
  retryStatusCode: 400 | 503;       // status to return on transient failure to trigger retry
}

export interface NormalizedOrderEvent {
  provider: ProviderId;
  externalOrderId: string;
  externalShopId: string;
  externalEventId?: string;
  status: 'pending' | 'paid' | 'partially_refunded' | 'refunded' | 'cancelled';
  currency: string;
  grossAmountCents: bigint;
  netAmountCents: bigint;
  lineItems: Array<{
    providerItemId?: string;
    ticketType: string;
    quantity: number;
    unitAmountCents: bigint;
    currency: string;
  }>;
  buyerEmailHash: string;
  buyerCountry?: string;
  placedAt: Date;
  paidAt?: Date;
  occurredAt: Date;
  attributionHint?: {
    trackerExternalId?: string;
    refParam?: string;
    utm?: { source?: string; medium?: string; campaign?: string; content?: string; term?: string };
  };
  rawMetadata?: Record<string, unknown>;
}

export interface CreateTrackerInput {
  campaignId: string;
  ambassadorId: string;
  shopExternalId: string;
  name: string;
  destinationContext?: { assetId?: string; label?: string };
}

export interface CreatedTracker {
  providerTrackerId: string;
  shopExternalId: string;
  destinationUrl: string;
  /** Provider-issued nonce for webhook authentication, if applicable. */
  webhookNonce?: string;
}

export interface ProviderCredentials {
  // Decrypted at use, never logged
  [key: string]: string | number;
}

export interface TicketingProvider {
  id: ProviderId;
  capabilities: ProviderCapabilities;

  // Tracker lifecycle
  createTracker?(input: CreateTrackerInput): Promise<CreatedTracker>;
  deleteTracker?(providerTrackerId: string): Promise<void>;

  // URL construction
  buildDestinationUrl(args: {
    baseUrl: string;
    nativeTracker?: { providerTrackerId: string };
    clickId: string;
    utm: { source: string; medium: string; campaign: string; content: string; term?: string };
  }): string;

  // Webhook authenticity (replaces verifyWebhookSignature)
  verifyWebhookAuthenticity?(args: {
    rawBody: string;
    headers: Headers;
    storedSecret: string;  // HMAC secret OR nonce, depending on capabilities.authenticity
  }): boolean;

  // Webhook parsing
  parseWebhook?(args: { rawBody: string; headers: Headers }): NormalizedOrderEvent | null;

  // Idempotency key derivation (use provider-supplied if available)
  deriveIdempotencyKey?(args: { rawBody: string; headers: Headers; parsed?: NormalizedOrderEvent }): string;

  // On-demand
  fetchOrder?(args: { externalOrderId: string; credentials: ProviderCredentials }): Promise<NormalizedOrderEvent | null>;

  // Reconciliation
  listOrdersSince?(args: { since: Date; credentials: ProviderCredentials }): AsyncIterable<NormalizedOrderEvent>;

  // Promo codes
  createDiscountCode?(args: {
    code: string;
    discountPercent?: number;
    discountAmountCents?: bigint;
    currency?: string;
    shopExternalId: string;
    credentials: ProviderCredentials;
  }): Promise<{ externalCodeId: string }>;

  // OAuth-based providers (Weeztix, Eventbrite, Shopify)
  oauth?: {
    authorizeUrl(args: { state: string; redirectUri: string }): string;
    exchangeCode(args: { code: string; redirectUri: string }): Promise<{
      accessToken: string;
      refreshToken: string;
      accessTokenExpiresAt: Date;
      refreshTokenExpiresAt?: Date;
    }>;
    refresh(args: { refreshToken: string }): Promise<{
      accessToken: string;
      refreshToken: string;
      accessTokenExpiresAt: Date;
      refreshTokenExpiresAt?: Date;
    }>;
  };
}
```

## Rules for adding a provider

1. Create `src/lib/providers/{provider}/index.ts` exporting a `TicketingProvider` implementation
2. Declare capabilities honestly. If the provider has webhooks but they're unsigned, set `webhooks: true` and document the nonce or IP-allowlist mitigation
3. Add a test fixture set in `src/lib/providers/{provider}/__fixtures__/` with at minimum: a paid order webhook, a refund webhook, a signature-failing payload
4. Add tests: authenticity verification, parse correctness, idempotency, refund cascade end-to-end
5. Register the provider in `src/lib/providers/registry.ts`
6. Add a migration row in `provider_connections` check constraint to allow the new id
7. Document in `docs/providers/{provider}.md`: auth flow, webhook setup steps, known quirks

## Weeztix (v1)

Reference: `docs/providers/weeztix.md` — authoritative for Weeztix-specific details. Read first.

**Capabilities:**

```ts
{
  nativeTrackers: true,
  webhooks: true,
  refundEvents: false,                       // refunds inferred from Order.updated
  refundInferenceField: 'invalidated_since', // confirmed in smoke test #9
  orderLookup: true,
  promoCodes: false,                          // deferred to post-MVP
  reconciliation: true,
  authenticity: { kind: 'nonce', header: 'OpenTicket-Identifier' },
  providerSuppliedIdempotencyHeader: 'OpenTicket-Dedupe-Key',
  retryStatusCode: 400,                       // Weeztix retries on 4xx, NOT 5xx
}
```

**Auth:** OAuth2 Authorization Code via `https://auth.openticket.tech/tokens`. Credentials from `apiteam@weeztix.com`. Access tokens expire in 3 days; refresh tokens last ~1 year. Refresh 6 hours before expiry via Inngest cron.

**Tracker creation:**
```
POST https://api.weeztix.com/trackers
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>
Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded

shop_id=<guid>&name=<name>&type=Other
```
Returns `{ guid, code, name, type, shop_id, created_at, updated_at }`. Store `guid` as `trackers.provider_tracker_id`. The tracker URL is `https://api.weeztix.com/<guid>` which 302s to the shop with attribution attached.

**Webhook creation:**
```
POST https://webhooks.weeztix.com/webhook
Authorization: Bearer <access_token>

name=<descriptive>&url=<our_endpoint>&resource=order&trigger=paid&retries=3
```
Subscribe to `order.paid` and `order.updated` separately. Store the returned nonce (in the creation response) per subscription. Webhook URL uses our per-connection secret URL token: `https://ravo.fm/api/webhooks/weeztix/{url_token}/`.

**Webhook headers received:**
- `OpenTicket-Identifier` — nonce, verify against stored value
- `OpenTicket-Dedupe-Key` — idempotency key, use directly
- `OpenTicket-Trigger` — event type, e.g. `order.paid`, `order.updated`
- `User-Agent: OpenTicket/Webhook`
- `Content-Type: application/json`

**Payload shape (Order trigger):** see `docs/providers/weeztix.md`. Key fields for normalization:
- `guid` → `externalOrderId`
- `shop_id` → `externalShopId`
- `currency` → `currency`
- `price` (cents) → `grossAmountCents`
- `value` + `service_fee` → use `price` as the source of truth for gross
- `status` → mapped to our normalized status
- `email` → SHA-256 hash → `buyerEmailHash`
- `firstname`, `lastname` → discarded (PII rule)
- `tracking_info.tracker_id` → `attributionHint.trackerExternalId`
- `tracking_info.click_id` → `attributionHint.refParam`
- `tracking_info.utm_*` → `attributionHint.utm`
- `tracking_info.purchaser_ip_address` → truncate to /24, derive country, discard
- `tickets[]` → mapped to line items
- `created_at` → `placedAt`
- `payment.status === 'completed'` ? → `paidAt = updated_at`

**Refund detection on `order.updated`:** check `invalidated_since` (non-null = refund) OR `returns` (non-null = refund). Smoke test confirms exact semantics; document in `docs/providers/weeztix.md`.

**Reconciliation:** confirm via smoke test whether `/orders` supports time-range filters. If yes, daily fetch of last 7 days; if no, escalate to Weeztix.

## Manual UTM (v1, universal fallback)

- `capabilities`: all false except `reconciliation: false`; `authenticity: { kind: 'none' }`; `retryStatusCode: 503`
- No native trackers, no webhooks, no auth flow
- The festival pastes the destination URL into Ravo
- `buildDestinationUrl` appends UTMs + `ref` to whatever URL the festival provided
- Conversion data comes from either:
  - A tracking pixel they paste on their thank-you page (POSTs to `/api/webhooks/pixel/{token}`)
  - A CSV upload via admin UI (parsed, normalized, fed into the same attribution pipeline)
  - A Zapier/Make bridge they configure pointing to our generic webhook endpoint
- UI labels Manual UTM data as **"estimated"** vs **"verified"** for native integrations
- Tier 4 attribution policy applies; cash rewards default to `requires_confirmation`

## Credential handling

- Store encrypted in `provider_connections.credentials_encrypted` (bytea) using pgsodium or Supabase Vault
- Decrypt only at the moment of use, inside the provider implementation
- Never log credentials, never include them in error messages
- Rotate by inserting a new credential and marking the old one `status = 'rotating'`, dual-run for a grace period, then disable old

## Health checks

Every provider integration includes a `healthcheck` method called by an Inngest job every 15 minutes:
- For webhook-based providers: assert the webhook URL is reachable from their side (some providers expose this; for others, check time since last webhook delivery — if >24h on a known-active campaign, raise alert)
- For polling/fetch-based: make a trivial authenticated API call

Result writes to `provider_connections.last_healthcheck_at` and `.status`. Status transitions raise notifications to org admins per `notification_preferences`.

## Never do

- Hard-code provider logic outside `src/lib/providers/{provider}/`
- Add `if (provider === 'weeztix') ...` branches in attribution or rewards engines
- Skip the capability check before calling an optional method
- Trust webhook payloads without verification + idempotency check (see `06-webhooks.mdc`)
- Log raw credentials, webhook nonces, or URL secrets
